manipulate

First we’re going to read in the California current data from the ERDDAP server https://oceanview.pfeg.noaa.gov/erddap/index.html could use ERDDAP to filter and select but we’re going to use the most basic version so that we can filter it ourselves.

Read online table, download to (*.csv)

# set variables
csv_url  <- "https://oceanview.pfeg.noaa.gov/erddap/tabledap/cciea_AC.csv"
dir_data <- "data"

# derived variables
csv <- file.path(dir_data, basename(csv_url))

# create directory
#only need to do once
#dir.create(dir_data)

# download file
if (!file.exists(csv))
  download.file(csv_url, csv)

Read table

# attempt to read csv
d <- read.csv(csv)
